> We’re a traditional bunch here at the Fresh Farm. Luke has often been known to throw
> his jacket into a puddle to save a lady’s slippers, whilst in spite of his tender
> years Ed insists on dressing like a man 30 years his senior. That’s why we decided
> to use chipotle, a smoky chilli paste produced by local farmers in the Oaxaca
> region of Mexico, who use age-old methods to work the land and produce this rich,
> sweet, spicy concoction. Add bit by bit, it’s hot!

== Rice ==

Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for your rice. Wash the @brown basmati
rice{1%cup} in a #sieve{} under running water for ~{1%minute}.

Boil the rice for ~{25%minutes} then drain and put back in the pot. Cover with a
#tea towel{} and leave off the heat until ready to serve.

== Chilli ==

Peel and cut the @red onion{1} lengthways through the root. Finely slice the onion
into half moon shapes.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Once hot add the
onion with @salt{1/4%tsp} and some @black pepper{}. Stir the onions and place a
#lid{} on the frying pan.

After ~{5%minutes} take the lid off the pan and add the @cumin{1/2%tsp} and
@tomato purée{1%tbsp} and stir everything together.

After ~{1%minute} add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and turn the heat to
medium.

> If you have any sugar in the cupboard add ½ tsp now.

Drain and rinse the kidney beans and the black beans. Add
@red kidney beans{1/2%400g can}(drained and rinsed) and
@organic black beans{1/2%400g can}(drained and rinsed) to the pan. Add
@vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Lastly add the @chipotle paste{1%tsp} - go carefully, it's
hot! Simmer on a low heat for ~{5-10%minutes} or until the rice is cooked.

== Citrus Crème Fraîche ==

Meanwhile, zest the @lime{1/2} and mix a pinch of the zest and a little squeeze of
the juice into the @crème fraîche{100%g}.

> When zesting (i.e. grating) the lime, don't go down to the white part underneath
> the skin as this tastes bitter.

Serve your chilli with the rice, a good dollop of crème fraîche and a big squeeze
of fresh lime juice.